S

setExecutePath(String) - Method in enum org.jtestdb.selenium.jscov.JscovBrowserKind
Set the executable path for browser-kind. This is provided for OPERA as its Selenium launcher needs to be to an absolute path.
setOffCodeCoverage() - Method in class org.jtestdb.selenium.jscov.JscovTestUtil
Set the JscovTestUtil object to a not-active mode so that actual code-coverage does not happen. HOWEVER, the test case script do not need to be changed in their use of start, store-report and stop method calls.
setOffViewReport() - Method in class org.jtestdb.selenium.jscov.JscovTestUtil
Set the view-report state to OFF when the viewReportDo method is invoked within the test-scripts. The view-report will not popup.
setOnCodeCoverage() - Method in class org.jtestdb.selenium.jscov.JscovTestUtil
Set the JscovTestUtil object to an active mode so that code-coverage capture will happen as the start, store-report and stop methods are invoked.
setOnViewReport() - Method in class org.jtestdb.selenium.jscov.JscovTestUtil
Set the view-report state to ON when the viewReportDo method is invoked within the test-scripts. This will result in an independent process being launched and popup a browser to the "reports".
SetTestMode - Class in org.jtestdb.selenium.tstmod
Class to set a web-page under test via a test-mode-element being added to some 'normal' element within the page.
SetTestMode(String, String, WebDriver) - Constructor for class org.jtestdb.selenium.tstmod.SetTestMode
Create a set test-mode processor object, with information/data included in the element's innerHTML text.
SetTestMode(String, WebDriver) - Constructor for class org.jtestdb.selenium.tstmod.SetTestMode
Create a set test-mode processor object, as a flag/semaphore.
startProxyServer() - Method in class org.jtestdb.selenium.jscov.JscovTestUtil
Start the proxy-server, checking that resources are in place. Start may be called many times, only the first one will do the actual start.
stopProxyServer(int) - Method in class org.jtestdb.selenium.jscov.JscovTestUtil
Stop the proxy-server running but first perform a 'store-report' action to create/append code-coverage to the reports directory.
storeJscoverReport(int) - Method in class org.jtestdb.selenium.jscov.JscovTestUtil
Store the report into the JSCover-structure-directory as provided in the report-directory provided via the constructor methods. JSCover support the automatic merging of reports while reporting into the same directories, this allows multiple store-report calls allowed.
